flowchart TD

subgraph S0 Configuration
A[config.py]
A1[Stores paths constants calibration values smoothing settings friction values plot settings]
A --> A1
end

subgraph S1 Input_Data
B[Raw JSON logs]
B1[Contain time commanded motion actual motion load voltage current end effector data metadata]
C[data_loader.py]
C1[Reads one JSON file and returns arrays and metadata dictionaries]
B --> B1 --> C --> C1
end

subgraph S2 Preprocessing
D[utils.py ticks_to_radians]
D1[Converts encoder ticks to joint angles in radians using direction and center offset]
E[utils.py fix_timestamps]
E1[Fixes duplicate or non increasing timestamps]
F[utils.py numerical_velocity]
F1[Computes joint velocity from position and time then smooths it]
G[utils.py numerical_acceleration]
G1[Computes joint acceleration from velocity and time then smooths it]
C1 --> D --> D1
C1 --> E --> E1
D1 --> F --> F1 --> G --> G1
end

subgraph S3 Torque_Measurements
H[torque.py torque_from_load_raw]
H1[Converts servo load register and voltage into raw torque in servo frame]
I[torque.py torque_from_load]
I1[Applies joint direction mapping and converts load torque into URDF frame]
J[torque.py torque_from_current]
J1[Converts motor current into estimated torque using torque constant]
C1 --> H --> H1 --> I --> I1
C1 --> J --> J1
end

subgraph S4 Robot_Model
K[torque.py build_pinocchio_model]
K1[Processes xacro and builds URDF model in Pinocchio]
K2[Loads kinematic tree joint structure masses centers of mass and inertias]
K3[Applies global mass scaling to link masses and inertias]
K4[Optionally adds extra masses]
A --> K
K --> K1 --> K2
K --> K3
K --> K4
end

subgraph S5 Analytical_Torque
L[torque.py torque_from_urdf]
L1[Uses actual joint angles]
L2[Uses numerical velocity and acceleration]
L3[Runs RNEA at every timestep]
L4[Outputs full analytical torque]
M[torque.py torque_gravity_only]
M1[Runs RNEA with zero velocity and zero acceleration]
M2[Outputs gravity only torque]
D1 --> L
F1 --> L
G1 --> L
K2 --> L
K3 --> L
L --> L1
L --> L2
L --> L3
L --> L4
D1 --> M
K2 --> M
K3 --> M
M --> M1 --> M2
end

subgraph S6 Friction_Model
N[torque.py smooth_sign]
N1[Uses tanh shape to avoid discontinuity near zero velocity]
O[torque.py torque_friction]
O1[Computes coulomb friction plus viscous friction from joint velocity]
F1 --> N --> N1 --> O --> O1
A --> O
end

subgraph S7 Single_File_Pipeline
P[main.py]
P1[Loads one log file]
P2[Converts actual positions to radians]
P3[Builds Pinocchio model]
P4[Computes load torque]
P5[Computes URDF analytical torque]
P6[Computes gravity only torque]
P7[Computes friction torque]
P8[Combines rigid body torque and friction]
P9[Computes residual between measured torque and analytical torque]
C --> P
D --> P
K --> P
I --> P
L --> P
M --> P
O --> P
P --> P1
P --> P2
P --> P3
P --> P4
P --> P5
P --> P6
P --> P7
P --> P8
P --> P9
end

subgraph S8 Diagnostics
Q[diagnostics.py]
Q1[Checks Pinocchio joint order against logged joint mapping]
Q2[Prints masses centers of mass and inertias]
Q3[Checks gravity torque at sample poses]
Q4[Checks joint angle ranges]
Q5[Checks timestamp quality]
Q6[Checks velocity and acceleration magnitudes]
Q7[Checks raw load and voltage ranges]
Q8[Checks current sign against load sign]
Q9[Compares torque magnitudes across methods]
P --> Q
Q --> Q1
Q --> Q2
Q --> Q3
Q --> Q4
Q --> Q5
Q --> Q6
Q --> Q7
Q --> Q8
Q --> Q9
end

subgraph S9 Plotting
R[plots.py]
R1[Plots measured torque against URDF torque and URDF plus friction]
R2[Plots residual that remains after analytical model]
R3[Plots gravity only torque against full RNEA]
R4[Plots joint angles velocities accelerations raw signals and end effector motion]
P --> R
R --> R1
R --> R2
R --> R3
R --> R4
end

subgraph S10 Mass_Calibration
S[calibrate_v2.py]
S1[Uses gravity only torque to calibrate global mass scale]
S2[Tests sign conventions for load torque mapping]
S3[Fits one global scale using joints with strongest gravity signal]
S4[Reports implied physical density and compares hypotheses]
M --> S
I --> S
S --> S1
S --> S2
S --> S3
S --> S4
end

subgraph S11 Friction_Calibration
T[calibrate_friction.py]
T1[Builds friction signal as measured torque minus URDF torque]
T2[Runs velocity statistics and correlation diagnostics]
T3[Uses regime analysis for direct estimates]
T4[Uses asymmetry analysis to separate friction from gravity bias]
T5[Uses epsilon sweep with bias aware least squares]
T6[Uses nonlinear fitting with physical bounds]
T7[Checks consistency across many trajectories]
T8[Synthesizes final recommended friction parameters]
I --> T
L --> T
S --> T
T --> T1
T --> T2
T --> T3
T --> T4
T --> T5
T --> T6
T --> T7
T --> T8
end

subgraph S12 Bulk_Processing
U[bulk_analyze.py]
U1[Finds all JSON files]
U2[Builds model once]
U3[Processes each file through the analytical torque pipeline]
U4[Generates one plot per file]
U5[Builds one global summary JSON with aggregate statistics]
V[plots_bulk.py]
V1[Provides headless save only plotting functions for batch runs]
U --> U1
U --> U2
U --> U3
U --> U4
U --> U5
U --> V
V --> V1
end

subgraph S13 Package_File
W[__init__.py]
W1[Marks Torque Analysis as a Python package]
W --> W1
end

subgraph S14 Core_Concept
X[Simple analytical model]
X1[Uses only rigid body inverse dynamics from URDF]
X2[Misses gearbox friction mass mismatch and unmodeled effects]
Y[Improved analytical model]
Y1[Adds friction model on top of rigid body torque]
Y2[Reduces systematic velocity dependent error]
Z[Residual for learning]
Z1[What remains after subtracting analytical model from measured torque]
Z2[Contains unmodeled dynamics calibration error and noise]
L --> X
X --> X1
X --> X2
O --> Y
L --> Y
Y --> Y1
Y --> Y2
P --> Z
Z --> Z1
Z --> Z2
end